  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "helper_1",
      "instructions": "Determine if there exists an integer n such that 2023*n is a power of 2. Use the prime factorization of 2023 to justify your answer. This corresponds to checking if k(n)=1 is possible."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_2",
      "instructions": "Determine if k(n)=2 is possible by checking if 2023 divides 2^a + 2^b for some integers a, b. Specifically, check if 2023 divides 2^m + 1 for some m. If k(n)=2 is impossible, investigate if k(n)=3 is possible (i.e., check if 2023 divides 2^a + 2^b + 2^c)."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "The parent will take the results from both helpers to find the smallest k(n). If helper_1 finds k(n)=1 is possible, the answer is 1. If helper_1 says no and helper_2 finds k(n)=2 is possible, the answer is 2. If both are impossible, the answer is the smallest k(n) found by helper_2 (likely 3)."
}
```

